<item>
            <title>[LU-19734] mgc_apply_recover_logs() to check import instances immediately</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19734</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The mgc_apply_recover_logs() can be improved in two ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&#160;instead of creating artificial LCFG_PARAM to set import connection via debugfs that can be done immediately as import is accessible in this function directly. That reduces code complexity in this area and reduces pressure on other parameters from configuration, e.g. &apos;params&apos; config being applied via process_param2_config()-&amp;gt;kobject_uevent_env() call chain&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;obdname creation can do part of work once but not on each entry, also making code cleaner there&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
